  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Student Care Teacher (SC)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for people, who are passionate about education and nurturing young children, to join our team!</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Position available: Student Care Teacher to guide primary school children on English,Chinese, Math and Science.</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage students and proactively respond to their developmental needs</li><li>Ensure classroom discipline and safety of children at all times</li><li>Deliver and present lesson content to children</li><li>Provide guidance and supervision for Primary School children on the completion of daily homework and spelling</li><li>Plan and prepare enrichment programmes/ activities with other teachers</li><li>Regular liaison with parents regarding children's progress and behaviour</li><li>Assist with other administrative tasks</li><li>Make a difference to our students' developmental years</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements & Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Possess genuine love to care and mentor children</li><li>WSQ Student Care or qualifications in field of community & social services is an advantage</li><li>Minimum 1 year of relevant working experience.</li><li>Good communication skills and must be team player</li><li>Great sense of responsibility</li></ul><p><strong>Salary:</strong></p><ul><li>$2,200 - $2,600</li></ul><p>Interested applicants, please send in your resume. Do include your reasons of leaving, expected salary, last drawn salary and date of availability to commence work.</p><p><br /></p><p>We seek your understanding that only shortlisted candidate will be notified. Thank you.</p>",
